37/* Used for writing a temporary charstring */
38struct str_encoder_t
39{
40 str_encoder_t (str_buff_t &buff_)
41 : buff (buff_) {}
42
43 void reset () { buff.reset (); }
44
45 void encode_byte (unsigned char b)
46 {
47 if (likely ((signed) buff.length < buff.allocated))
48 buff.arrayZ[buff.length++] = b;
49 else
50 buff.push (v&: b);
51 }
52
53 void encode_int (int v)
54 {
55 if ((-1131 <= v) && (v <= 1131))
56 {
57 if ((-107 <= v) && (v <= 107))
58 encode_byte (b: v + 139);
59 else if (v > 0)
60 {
61 v -= 108;
62 encode_byte (b: (v >> 8) + OpCode_TwoBytePosInt0);
63 encode_byte (b: v & 0xFF);
64 }
65 else
66 {
67 v = -v - 108;
68 encode_byte (b: (v >> 8) + OpCode_TwoByteNegInt0);
69 encode_byte (b: v & 0xFF);
70 }
71 }
72 else
73 {
74 if (unlikely (v < -32768))
75 v = -32768;
76 else if (unlikely (v > 32767))
77 v = 32767;
78 encode_byte (OpCode_shortint);
79 encode_byte (b: (v >> 8) & 0xFF);
80 encode_byte (b: v & 0xFF);
81 }
82 }
83
84 // Encode number for CharString
85 void encode_num_cs (const number_t& n)
86 {
87 if (n.in_int_range ())
88 {
89 encode_int (v: n.to_int ());
90 }
91 else
92 {
93 int32_t v = n.to_fixed ();
94 encode_byte (OpCode_fixedcs);
95 encode_byte (b: (v >> 24) & 0xFF);
96 encode_byte (b: (v >> 16) & 0xFF);
97 encode_byte (b: (v >> 8) & 0xFF);
98 encode_byte (b: v & 0xFF);
99 }
100 }
101
102 // Encode number for TopDict / Private
103 void encode_num_tp (const number_t& n)
104 {
105 if (n.in_int_range ())
106 {
107 // TODO longint
108 encode_int (v: n.to_int ());
109 }
110 else
111 {
112 // Sigh. BCD
113 // https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/opentype/spec/cff2#table-5-nibble-definitions
114 double v = n.to_real ();
115 encode_byte (OpCode_BCD);
116
117 // Based on:
118 // https://github.com/fonttools/fonttools/blob/97ed3a61cde03e17b8be36f866192fbd56f1d1a7/Lib/fontTools/misc/psCharStrings.py#L265-L294
119
120 char buf[16];
121 /* FontTools has the following comment:
122 *
123 * # Note: 14 decimal digits seems to be the limitation for CFF real numbers
124 * # in macOS. However, we use 8 here to match the implementation of AFDKO.
125 *
126 * We use 8 here to match FontTools X-).
127 */
128
129 hb_locale_t clocale HB_UNUSED;
130 hb_locale_t oldlocale HB_UNUSED;
131 oldlocale = hb_uselocale (clocale = newlocale (LC_ALL_MASK, "C", NULL));
132 snprintf (s: buf, maxlen: sizeof (buf), format: "%.8G", v);
133 (void) hb_uselocale (((void) freelocale (clocale), oldlocale));
134
135 char *s = buf;
136 if (s[0] == '0' && s[1] == '.')
137 s++;
138 else if (s[0] == '-' && s[1] == '0' && s[2] == '.')
139 {
140 s[1] = '-';
141 s++;
142 }
143 hb_vector_t<char> nibbles;
144 while (*s)
145 {
146 char c = s[0];
147 s++;
148
149 switch (c)
150 {
151 case 'E':
152 {
153 char c2 = *s;
154 if (c2 == '-')
155 {
156 s++;
157 nibbles.push (v: 0x0C); // E-
158 continue;
159 }
160 if (c2 == '+')
161 s++;
162 nibbles.push (v: 0x0B); // E
163 continue;
164 }
165
166 case '.': case ',': // Comma for some European locales in case no uselocale available.
167 nibbles.push (v: 0x0A); // .
168 continue;
169
170 case '-':
171 nibbles.push (v: 0x0E); // .
172 continue;
173 }
174
175 nibbles.push (v: c - '0');
176 }
177 nibbles.push (v: 0x0F);
178 if (nibbles.length % 2)
179 nibbles.push (v: 0x0F);
180
181 unsigned count = nibbles.length;
182 for (unsigned i = 0; i < count; i += 2)
183 encode_byte (b: (nibbles[i] << 4) | nibbles[i+1]);
184 }
185 }
186
187 void encode_op (op_code_t op)
188 {
189 if (Is_OpCode_ESC (op))
190 {
191 encode_byte (OpCode_escape);
192 encode_byte (b: Unmake_OpCode_ESC (op));
193 }
194 else
195 encode_byte (b: op);
196 }
197
198 void copy_str (const unsigned char *str, unsigned length)
199 {
200 assert ((signed) (buff.length + length) <= buff.allocated);
201 hb_memcpy (dst: buff.arrayZ + buff.length, src: str, len: length);
202 buff.length += length;
203 }
204
205 bool in_error () const { return buff.in_error (); }
206
207 protected:
208
209 str_buff_t &buff;
210};

225template <typename OPSTR=op_str_t>
226struct cff_top_dict_op_serializer_t : op_serializer_t
227{
228 bool serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c,
229 const OPSTR &opstr,
230 const cff_sub_table_info_t &info) const
231 {
232 TRACE_SERIALIZE (this);
233
234 switch (opstr.op)
235 {
236 case OpCode_CharStrings:
237 return_trace (FontDict::serialize_link4_op(c, opstr.op, info.char_strings_link, whence_t::Absolute));
238
239 case OpCode_FDArray:
240 return_trace (FontDict::serialize_link4_op(c, opstr.op, info.fd_array_link, whence_t::Absolute));
241
242 case OpCode_FDSelect:
243 return_trace (FontDict::serialize_link4_op(c, opstr.op, info.fd_select.link, whence_t::Absolute));
244
245 default:
246 return_trace (copy_opstr (c, opstr));
247 }
248 return_trace (true);
249 }
250};
251
252struct cff_font_dict_op_serializer_t : op_serializer_t
253{
254 bool serialize (hb_serialize_context_t *c,
255 const op_str_t &opstr,
256 const table_info_t &privateDictInfo) const
257 {
258 TRACE_SERIALIZE (this);
259
260 if (opstr.op == OpCode_Private)
261 {
262 /* serialize the private dict size & offset as 2-byte & 4-byte integers */
263 return_trace (UnsizedByteStr::serialize_int2 (c, privateDictInfo.size) &&
264 Dict::serialize_link4_op (c, opstr.op, privateDictInfo.link, whence_t::Absolute));
265 }
266 else
267 {
268 unsigned char *d = c->allocate_size<unsigned char> (size: opstr.length);
269 if (unlikely (!d)) return_trace (false);
270 /* Faster than hb_memcpy for small strings. */
271 for (unsigned i = 0; i < opstr.length; i++)
272 d[i] = opstr.ptr[i];
273 //hb_memcpy (d, opstr.ptr, opstr.length);
274 }
275 return_trace (true);
276 }
277};

286template <typename ACC, typename ENV, typename OPSET, op_code_t endchar_op=OpCode_Invalid>
287struct subr_flattener_t
288{
289 subr_flattener_t (const ACC &acc_,
290 const hb_subset_plan_t *plan_)
291 : acc (acc_), plan (plan_) {}
292
293 bool flatten (str_buff_vec_t &flat_charstrings)
294 {
295 unsigned count = plan->num_output_glyphs ();
296 if (!flat_charstrings.resize_exact (size_: count))
297 return false;
298 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < count; i++)
299 {
300 hb_codepoint_t glyph;
301 if (!plan->old_gid_for_new_gid (new_gid: i, old_gid: &glyph))
302 {
303 /* add an endchar only charstring for a missing glyph if CFF1 */
304 if (endchar_op != OpCode_Invalid) flat_charstrings[i].push (v: endchar_op);
305 continue;
306 }
307 const hb_ubytes_t str = (*acc.charStrings)[glyph];
308 unsigned int fd = acc.fdSelect->get_fd (glyph);
309 if (unlikely (fd >= acc.fdCount))
310 return false;
311
312
313 ENV env (str, acc, fd,
314 plan->normalized_coords.arrayZ, plan->normalized_coords.length);
315 cs_interpreter_t<ENV, OPSET, flatten_param_t> interp (env);
316 flatten_param_t param = {
317 .flatStr: flat_charstrings.arrayZ[i],
318 .drop_hints: (bool) (plan->flags & HB_SUBSET_FLAGS_NO_HINTING),
319 .plan: plan
320 };
321 if (unlikely (!interp.interpret (param)))
322 return false;
323 }
324 return true;
325 }
326
327 const ACC &acc;
328 const hb_subset_plan_t *plan;
329};

368struct parsed_cs_str_t : parsed_values_t<parsed_cs_op_t>
369{
370 parsed_cs_str_t () :
371 parsed (false),
372 hint_dropped (false),
373 has_prefix_ (false),
374 has_calls_ (false)
375 {
376 SUPER::init ();
377 }
378
379 void add_op (op_code_t op, const byte_str_ref_t& str_ref)
380 {
381 if (!is_parsed ())
382 SUPER::add_op (op, str_ref);
383 }
384
385 void add_call_op (op_code_t op, const byte_str_ref_t& str_ref, unsigned int subr_num)
386 {
387 if (!is_parsed ())
388 {
389 has_calls_ = true;
390
391 /* Pop the subroutine number. */
392 values.pop ();
393
394 SUPER::add_op (op, str_ref, v: {subr_num});
395 }
396 }
397
398 void set_prefix (const number_t &num, op_code_t op = OpCode_Invalid)
399 {
400 has_prefix_ = true;
401 prefix_op_ = op;
402 prefix_num_ = num;
403 }
404
405 bool at_end (unsigned int pos) const
406 {
407 return ((pos + 1 >= values.length) /* CFF2 */
408 || (values[pos + 1].op == OpCode_return));
409 }
410
411 bool is_parsed () const { return parsed; }
412 void set_parsed () { parsed = true; }
413
414 bool is_hint_dropped () const { return hint_dropped; }
415 void set_hint_dropped () { hint_dropped = true; }
416
417 bool is_vsindex_dropped () const { return vsindex_dropped; }
418 void set_vsindex_dropped () { vsindex_dropped = true; }
419
420 bool has_prefix () const { return has_prefix_; }
421 op_code_t prefix_op () const { return prefix_op_; }
422 const number_t &prefix_num () const { return prefix_num_; }
423
424 bool has_calls () const { return has_calls_; }
425
426 void compact ()
427 {
428 unsigned count = values.length;
429 if (!count) return;
430 auto &opstr = values.arrayZ;
431 unsigned j = 0;
432 for (unsigned i = 1; i < count; i++)
433 {
434 /* See if we can combine op j and op i. */
435 bool combine =
436 (opstr[j].op != OpCode_callsubr && opstr[j].op != OpCode_callgsubr) &&
437 (opstr[i].op != OpCode_callsubr && opstr[i].op != OpCode_callgsubr) &&
438 (opstr[j].is_hinting () == opstr[i].is_hinting ()) &&
439 (opstr[j].ptr + opstr[j].length == opstr[i].ptr) &&
440 (opstr[j].length + opstr[i].length <= 255);
441
442 if (combine)
443 {
444 opstr[j].length += opstr[i].length;
445 opstr[j].op = OpCode_Invalid;
446 }
447 else
448 {
449 opstr[++j] = opstr[i];
450 }
451 }
452 values.shrink (size_: j + 1);
453 }
454
455 protected:
456 bool parsed : 1;
457 bool hint_dropped : 1;
458 bool vsindex_dropped : 1;
459 bool has_prefix_ : 1;
460 bool has_calls_ : 1;
461 op_code_t prefix_op_;
462 number_t prefix_num_;
463
464 private:
465 typedef parsed_values_t<parsed_cs_op_t> SUPER;
466};

474struct cff_subset_accelerator_t
475{
476 static cff_subset_accelerator_t* create (
477 hb_blob_t* original_blob,
478 const parsed_cs_str_vec_t& parsed_charstrings,
479 const parsed_cs_str_vec_t& parsed_global_subrs,
480 const hb_vector_t<parsed_cs_str_vec_t>& parsed_local_subrs) {
481 cff_subset_accelerator_t* accel =
482 (cff_subset_accelerator_t*) hb_malloc (size: sizeof(cff_subset_accelerator_t));
483 new (accel) cff_subset_accelerator_t (original_blob,
484 parsed_charstrings,
485 parsed_global_subrs,
486 parsed_local_subrs);
487 return accel;
488 }
489
490 static void destroy (void* value) {
491 if (!value) return;
492
493 cff_subset_accelerator_t* accel = (cff_subset_accelerator_t*) value;
494 accel->~cff_subset_accelerator_t ();
495 hb_free (ptr: accel);
496 }
497
498 cff_subset_accelerator_t(
499 hb_blob_t* original_blob_,
500 const parsed_cs_str_vec_t& parsed_charstrings_,
501 const parsed_cs_str_vec_t& parsed_global_subrs_,
502 const hb_vector_t<parsed_cs_str_vec_t>& parsed_local_subrs_)
503 {
504 parsed_charstrings = parsed_charstrings_;
505 parsed_global_subrs = parsed_global_subrs_;
506 parsed_local_subrs = parsed_local_subrs_;
507
508 // the parsed charstrings point to memory in the original CFF table so we must hold a reference
509 // to it to keep the memory valid.
510 original_blob = hb_blob_reference (blob: original_blob_);
511 }
512
513 ~cff_subset_accelerator_t() {
514 hb_blob_destroy (blob: original_blob);
515 hb_map_destroy (map: glyph_to_sid_map.get_relaxed ());
516 }
517
518 parsed_cs_str_vec_t parsed_charstrings;
519 parsed_cs_str_vec_t parsed_global_subrs;
520 hb_vector_t<parsed_cs_str_vec_t> parsed_local_subrs;
521 mutable hb_atomic_ptr_t<hb_map_t> glyph_to_sid_map = nullptr;
522
523 private:
524 hb_blob_t* original_blob;
525};

527struct subr_subset_param_t
528{
529 subr_subset_param_t (parsed_cs_str_t *parsed_charstring_,
530 parsed_cs_str_vec_t *parsed_global_subrs_,
531 parsed_cs_str_vec_t *parsed_local_subrs_,
532 hb_set_t *global_closure_,
533 hb_set_t *local_closure_,
534 bool drop_hints_) :
535 current_parsed_str (parsed_charstring_),
536 parsed_charstring (parsed_charstring_),
537 parsed_global_subrs (parsed_global_subrs_),
538 parsed_local_subrs (parsed_local_subrs_),
539 global_closure (global_closure_),
540 local_closure (local_closure_),
541 drop_hints (drop_hints_) {}
542
543 parsed_cs_str_t *get_parsed_str_for_context (call_context_t &context)
544 {
545 switch (context.type)
546 {
547 case CSType_CharString:
548 return parsed_charstring;
549
550 case CSType_LocalSubr:
551 if (likely (context.subr_num < parsed_local_subrs->length))
552 return &(*parsed_local_subrs)[context.subr_num];
553 break;
554
555 case CSType_GlobalSubr:
556 if (likely (context.subr_num < parsed_global_subrs->length))
557 return &(*parsed_global_subrs)[context.subr_num];
558 break;
559 }
560 return nullptr;
561 }
562
563 template <typename ENV>
564 void set_current_str (ENV &env, bool calling)
565 {
566 parsed_cs_str_t *parsed_str = get_parsed_str_for_context (context&: env.context);
567 if (unlikely (!parsed_str))
568 {
569 env.set_error ();
570 return;
571 }
572 /* If the called subroutine is parsed partially but not completely yet,
573 * it must be because we are calling it recursively.
574 * Handle it as an error. */
575 if (unlikely (calling && !parsed_str->is_parsed () && (parsed_str->values.length > 0)))
576 env.set_error ();
577 else
578 {
579 if (!parsed_str->is_parsed ())
580 parsed_str->alloc (n: env.str_ref.total_size ());
581 current_parsed_str = parsed_str;
582 }
583 }
584
585 parsed_cs_str_t *current_parsed_str;
586
587 parsed_cs_str_t *parsed_charstring;
588 parsed_cs_str_vec_t *parsed_global_subrs;
589 parsed_cs_str_vec_t *parsed_local_subrs;
590 hb_set_t *global_closure;
591 hb_set_t *local_closure;
592 bool drop_hints;
593};

595struct subr_remap_t : hb_inc_bimap_t
596{
597 void create (const hb_set_t *closure)
598 {
599 /* create a remapping of subroutine numbers from old to new.
600 * no optimization based on usage counts. fonttools doesn't appear doing that either.
601 */
602
603 resize (pop: closure->get_population ());
604 hb_codepoint_t old_num = HB_SET_VALUE_INVALID;
605 while (hb_set_next (set: closure, codepoint: &old_num))
606 add (lhs: old_num);
607
608 if (get_population () < 1240)
609 bias = 107;
610 else if (get_population () < 33900)
611 bias = 1131;
612 else
613 bias = 32768;
614 }
615
616 int biased_num (unsigned int old_num) const
617 {
618 hb_codepoint_t new_num = get (lhs: old_num);
619 return (int)new_num - bias;
620 }
621
622 protected:
623 int bias;
624};

649template <typename SUBSETTER, typename SUBRS, typename ACC, typename ENV, typename OPSET, op_code_t endchar_op=OpCode_Invalid>
650struct subr_subsetter_t
651{
652 subr_subsetter_t (ACC &acc_, const hb_subset_plan_t *plan_)
653 : acc (acc_), plan (plan_), closures(acc_.fdCount),
654 remaps(acc_.fdCount)
655 {}
656
657 /* Subroutine subsetting with --no-desubroutinize runs in phases:
658 *
659 * 1. execute charstrings/subroutines to determine subroutine closures
660 * 2. parse out all operators and numbers
661 * 3. mark hint operators and operands for removal if --no-hinting
662 * 4. re-encode all charstrings and subroutines with new subroutine numbers
663 *
664 * Phases #1 and #2 are done at the same time in collect_subrs ().
665 * Phase #3 walks charstrings/subroutines forward then backward (hence parsing required),
666 * because we can't tell if a number belongs to a hint op until we see the first moveto.
667 *
668 * Assumption: a callsubr/callgsubr operator must immediately follow a (biased) subroutine number
669 * within the same charstring/subroutine, e.g., not split across a charstring and a subroutine.
670 */
671 bool subset (void)
672 {
673 unsigned fd_count = acc.fdCount;
674 const cff_subset_accelerator_t* cff_accelerator = nullptr;
675 if (plan->accelerator && plan->accelerator->cff_accelerator) {
676 cff_accelerator = plan->accelerator->cff_accelerator;
677 fd_count = cff_accelerator->parsed_local_subrs.length;
678 }
679
680 if (cff_accelerator) {
681 // If we are not dropping hinting then charstrings are not modified so we can
682 // just use a reference to the cached copies.
683 cached_charstrings.resize_exact (size_: plan->num_output_glyphs ());
684 parsed_global_subrs = &cff_accelerator->parsed_global_subrs;
685 parsed_local_subrs = &cff_accelerator->parsed_local_subrs;
686 } else {
687 parsed_charstrings.resize_exact (size_: plan->num_output_glyphs ());
688 parsed_global_subrs_storage.resize_exact (size_: acc.globalSubrs->count);
689
690 if (unlikely (!parsed_local_subrs_storage.resize (fd_count))) return false;
691
692 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < acc.fdCount; i++)
693 {
694 unsigned count = acc.privateDicts[i].localSubrs->count;
695 parsed_local_subrs_storage[i].resize (size_: count);
696 if (unlikely (parsed_local_subrs_storage[i].in_error ())) return false;
697 }
698
699 parsed_global_subrs = &parsed_global_subrs_storage;
700 parsed_local_subrs = &parsed_local_subrs_storage;
701 }
702
703 if (unlikely (remaps.in_error()
704 || cached_charstrings.in_error ()
705 || parsed_charstrings.in_error ()
706 || parsed_global_subrs->in_error ()
707 || closures.in_error ())) {
708 return false;
709 }
710
711 /* phase 1 & 2 */
712 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < plan->num_output_glyphs (); i++)
713 {
714 hb_codepoint_t glyph;
715 if (!plan->old_gid_for_new_gid (new_gid: i, old_gid: &glyph))
716 continue;
717
718 const hb_ubytes_t str = (*acc.charStrings)[glyph];
719 unsigned int fd = acc.fdSelect->get_fd (glyph);
720 if (unlikely (fd >= acc.fdCount))
721 return false;
722
723 if (cff_accelerator)
724 {
725 // parsed string already exists in accelerator, copy it and move
726 // on.
727 if (cached_charstrings)
728 cached_charstrings[i] = &cff_accelerator->parsed_charstrings[glyph];
729 else
730 parsed_charstrings[i] = cff_accelerator->parsed_charstrings[glyph];
731
732 continue;
733 }
734
735 ENV env (str, acc, fd);
736 cs_interpreter_t<ENV, OPSET, subr_subset_param_t> interp (env);
737
738 parsed_charstrings[i].alloc (n: str.length);
739 subr_subset_param_t param (&parsed_charstrings[i],
740 &parsed_global_subrs_storage,
741 &parsed_local_subrs_storage[fd],
742 &closures.global_closure,
743 &closures.local_closures[fd],
744 plan->flags & HB_SUBSET_FLAGS_NO_HINTING);
745
746 if (unlikely (!interp.interpret (param)))
747 return false;
748
749 /* complete parsed string esp. copy CFF1 width or CFF2 vsindex to the parsed charstring for encoding */
750 SUBSETTER::complete_parsed_str (interp.env, param, parsed_charstrings[i]);
751
752 /* mark hint ops and arguments for drop */
753 if ((plan->flags & HB_SUBSET_FLAGS_NO_HINTING) || plan->inprogress_accelerator)
754 {
755 subr_subset_param_t param (&parsed_charstrings[i],
756 &parsed_global_subrs_storage,
757 &parsed_local_subrs_storage[fd],
758 &closures.global_closure,
759 &closures.local_closures[fd],
760 plan->flags & HB_SUBSET_FLAGS_NO_HINTING);
761
762 drop_hints_param_t drop;
763 if (drop_hints_in_str (str&: parsed_charstrings[i], param, drop))
764 {
765 parsed_charstrings[i].set_hint_dropped ();
766 if (drop.vsindex_dropped)
767 parsed_charstrings[i].set_vsindex_dropped ();
768 }
769 }
770
771 /* Doing this here one by one instead of compacting all at the en
772 * has massive peak-memory saving.
773 *
774 * The compacting both saves memory and makes further operations
775 * faster.
776 */
777 parsed_charstrings[i].compact ();
778 }
779
780 /* Since parsed strings were loaded from accelerator, we still need
781 * to compute the subroutine closures which would have normally happened during
782 * parsing.
783 *
784 * Or if we are dropping hinting, redo closure to get actually used subrs.
785 */
786 if ((cff_accelerator ||
787 (!cff_accelerator && plan->flags & HB_SUBSET_FLAGS_NO_HINTING)) &&
788 !closure_subroutines(global_subrs: *parsed_global_subrs,
789 local_subrs: *parsed_local_subrs))
790 return false;
791
792 remaps.create (closures);
793
794 populate_subset_accelerator ();
795 return true;
796 }
797
798 bool encode_charstrings (str_buff_vec_t &buffArray, bool encode_prefix = true) const
799 {
800 if (unlikely (!buffArray.resize_exact (plan->num_output_glyphs ())))
801 return false;
802 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < plan->num_output_glyphs (); i++)
803 {
804 hb_codepoint_t glyph;
805 if (!plan->old_gid_for_new_gid (new_gid: i, old_gid: &glyph))
806 {
807 /* add an endchar only charstring for a missing glyph if CFF1 */
808 if (endchar_op != OpCode_Invalid) buffArray.arrayZ[i].push (v: endchar_op);
809 continue;
810 }
811 unsigned int fd = acc.fdSelect->get_fd (glyph);
812 if (unlikely (fd >= acc.fdCount))
813 return false;
814 if (unlikely (!encode_str (get_parsed_charstring (i), fd, buffArray.arrayZ[i], encode_prefix)))
815 return false;
816 }
817 return true;
818 }
819
820 bool encode_subrs (const parsed_cs_str_vec_t &subrs, const subr_remap_t& remap, unsigned int fd, str_buff_vec_t &buffArray) const
821 {
822 unsigned int count = remap.get_population ();
823
824 if (unlikely (!buffArray.resize_exact (count)))
825 return false;
826 for (unsigned int new_num = 0; new_num < count; new_num++)
827 {
828 hb_codepoint_t old_num = remap.backward (rhs: new_num);
829 assert (old_num != CFF_UNDEF_CODE);
830
831 if (unlikely (!encode_str (subrs[old_num], fd, buffArray[new_num])))
832 return false;
833 }
834 return true;
835 }

847 protected:
848 struct drop_hints_param_t
849 {
850 drop_hints_param_t ()
851 : seen_moveto (false),
852 ends_in_hint (false),
853 all_dropped (false),
854 vsindex_dropped (false) {}
855
856 bool seen_moveto;
857 bool ends_in_hint;
858 bool all_dropped;
859 bool vsindex_dropped;
860 };
861
862 bool drop_hints_in_subr (parsed_cs_str_t &str, unsigned int pos,
863 parsed_cs_str_vec_t &subrs, unsigned int subr_num,
864 const subr_subset_param_t &param, drop_hints_param_t &drop)
865 {
866 drop.ends_in_hint = false;
867 bool has_hint = drop_hints_in_str (str&: subrs[subr_num], param, drop);
868
869 /* if this subr ends with a stem hint (i.e., not a number; potential argument for moveto),
870 * then this entire subroutine must be a hint. drop its call. */
871 if (drop.ends_in_hint)
872 {
873 str.values[pos].set_hinting ();
874 /* if this subr call is at the end of the parent subr, propagate the flag
875 * otherwise reset the flag */
876 if (!str.at_end (pos))
877 drop.ends_in_hint = false;
878 }
879 else if (drop.all_dropped)
880 {
881 str.values[pos].set_hinting ();
882 }
883
884 return has_hint;
885 }
886
887 /* returns true if it sees a hint op before the first moveto */
888 bool drop_hints_in_str (parsed_cs_str_t &str, const subr_subset_param_t &param, drop_hints_param_t &drop)
889 {
890 bool seen_hint = false;
891
892 unsigned count = str.values.length;
893 auto *values = str.values.arrayZ;
894 for (unsigned int pos = 0; pos < count; pos++)
895 {
896 bool has_hint = false;
897 switch (values[pos].op)
898 {
899 case OpCode_callsubr:
900 has_hint = drop_hints_in_subr (str, pos,
901 subrs&: *param.parsed_local_subrs, subr_num: values[pos].subr_num,
902 param, drop);
903 break;
904
905 case OpCode_callgsubr:
906 has_hint = drop_hints_in_subr (str, pos,
907 subrs&: *param.parsed_global_subrs, subr_num: values[pos].subr_num,
908 param, drop);
909 break;
910
911 case OpCode_rmoveto:
912 case OpCode_hmoveto:
913 case OpCode_vmoveto:
914 drop.seen_moveto = true;
915 break;
916
917 case OpCode_hintmask:
918 case OpCode_cntrmask:
919 if (drop.seen_moveto)
920 {
921 values[pos].set_hinting ();
922 break;
923 }
924 HB_FALLTHROUGH;
925
926 case OpCode_hstemhm:
927 case OpCode_vstemhm:
928 case OpCode_hstem:
929 case OpCode_vstem:
930 has_hint = true;
931 values[pos].set_hinting ();
932 if (str.at_end (pos))
933 drop.ends_in_hint = true;
934 break;
935
936 case OpCode_dotsection:
937 values[pos].set_hinting ();
938 break;
939
940 default:
941 /* NONE */
942 break;
943 }
944 if (has_hint)
945 {
946 for (int i = pos - 1; i >= 0; i--)
947 {
948 parsed_cs_op_t &csop = values[(unsigned)i];
949 if (csop.is_hinting ())
950 break;
951 csop.set_hinting ();
952 if (csop.op == OpCode_vsindexcs)
953 drop.vsindex_dropped = true;
954 }
955 seen_hint |= has_hint;
956 }
957 }
958
959 /* Raise all_dropped flag if all operators except return are dropped from a subr.
960 * It may happen even after seeing the first moveto if a subr contains
961 * only (usually one) hintmask operator, then calls to this subr can be dropped.
962 */
963 drop.all_dropped = true;
964 for (unsigned int pos = 0; pos < count; pos++)
965 {
966 parsed_cs_op_t &csop = values[pos];
967 if (csop.op == OpCode_return)
968 break;
969 if (!csop.is_hinting ())
970 {
971 drop.all_dropped = false;
972 break;
973 }
974 }
975
976 return seen_hint;
977 }
978
979 bool closure_subroutines (const parsed_cs_str_vec_t& global_subrs,
980 const hb_vector_t<parsed_cs_str_vec_t>& local_subrs)
981 {
982 closures.reset ();
983 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < plan->num_output_glyphs (); i++)
984 {
985 hb_codepoint_t glyph;
986 if (!plan->old_gid_for_new_gid (new_gid: i, old_gid: &glyph))
987 continue;
988 unsigned int fd = acc.fdSelect->get_fd (glyph);
989 if (unlikely (fd >= acc.fdCount))
990 return false;
991
992 // Note: const cast is safe here because the collect_subr_refs_in_str only performs a
993 // closure and does not modify any of the charstrings.
994 subr_subset_param_t param (const_cast<parsed_cs_str_t*> (&get_parsed_charstring (i)),
995 const_cast<parsed_cs_str_vec_t*> (&global_subrs),
996 const_cast<parsed_cs_str_vec_t*> (&local_subrs[fd]),
997 &closures.global_closure,
998 &closures.local_closures[fd],
999 plan->flags & HB_SUBSET_FLAGS_NO_HINTING);
1000 collect_subr_refs_in_str (str: get_parsed_charstring (i), param);
1001 }
1002
1003 return true;
1004 }
1005
1006 void collect_subr_refs_in_subr (unsigned int subr_num, parsed_cs_str_vec_t &subrs,
1007 hb_set_t *closure,
1008 const subr_subset_param_t &param)
1009 {
1010 if (closure->has (k: subr_num))
1011 return;
1012 closure->add (g: subr_num);
1013 collect_subr_refs_in_str (str: subrs[subr_num], param);
1014 }
1015
1016 void collect_subr_refs_in_str (const parsed_cs_str_t &str,
1017 const subr_subset_param_t &param)
1018 {
1019 if (!str.has_calls ())
1020 return;
1021
1022 for (auto &opstr : str.values)
1023 {
1024 if (!param.drop_hints || !opstr.is_hinting ())
1025 {
1026 switch (opstr.op)
1027 {
1028 case OpCode_callsubr:
1029 collect_subr_refs_in_subr (subr_num: opstr.subr_num, subrs&: *param.parsed_local_subrs,
1030 closure: param.local_closure, param);
1031 break;
1032
1033 case OpCode_callgsubr:
1034 collect_subr_refs_in_subr (subr_num: opstr.subr_num, subrs&: *param.parsed_global_subrs,
1035 closure: param.global_closure, param);
1036 break;
1037
1038 default: break;
1039 }
1040 }
1041 }
1042 }
1043
1044 bool encode_str (const parsed_cs_str_t &str, const unsigned int fd, str_buff_t &buff, bool encode_prefix = true) const
1045 {
1046 str_encoder_t encoder (buff);
1047 encoder.reset ();
1048 bool hinting = !(plan->flags & HB_SUBSET_FLAGS_NO_HINTING);
1049 /* if a prefix (CFF1 width or CFF2 vsindex) has been removed along with hints,
1050 * re-insert it at the beginning of charstreing */
1051 if (encode_prefix && str.has_prefix () && !hinting && str.is_hint_dropped ())
1052 {
1053 encoder.encode_num_cs (n: str.prefix_num ());
1054 if (str.prefix_op () != OpCode_Invalid)
1055 encoder.encode_op (op: str.prefix_op ());
1056 }
1057
1058 unsigned size = 0;
1059 for (auto &opstr : str.values)
1060 {
1061 size += opstr.length;
1062 if (opstr.op == OpCode_callsubr || opstr.op == OpCode_callgsubr)
1063 size += 3;
1064 }
1065 if (!buff.alloc (size: buff.length + size, exact: true))
1066 return false;
1067
1068 for (auto &opstr : str.values)
1069 {
1070 if (hinting || !opstr.is_hinting ())
1071 {
1072 switch (opstr.op)
1073 {
1074 case OpCode_callsubr:
1075 encoder.encode_int (v: remaps.local_remaps[fd].biased_num (old_num: opstr.subr_num));
1076 encoder.copy_str (str: opstr.ptr, length: opstr.length);
1077 break;
1078
1079 case OpCode_callgsubr:
1080 encoder.encode_int (v: remaps.global_remap.biased_num (old_num: opstr.subr_num));
1081 encoder.copy_str (str: opstr.ptr, length: opstr.length);
1082 break;
1083
1084 default:
1085 encoder.copy_str (str: opstr.ptr, length: opstr.length);
1086 break;
1087 }
1088 }
1089 }
1090 return !encoder.in_error ();
1091 }

1093 void compact_parsed_subrs () const
1094 {
1095 for (auto &cs : parsed_global_subrs_storage)
1096 cs.compact ();
1097 for (auto &vec : parsed_local_subrs_storage)
1098 for (auto &cs : vec)
1099 cs.compact ();
1100 }

1102 void populate_subset_accelerator () const
1103 {
1104 if (!plan->inprogress_accelerator) return;
1105
1106 compact_parsed_subrs ();
1107
1108 plan->inprogress_accelerator->cff_accelerator =
1109 cff_subset_accelerator_t::create(original_blob: acc.blob,
1110 parsed_charstrings,
1111 parsed_global_subrs: parsed_global_subrs_storage,
1112 parsed_local_subrs: parsed_local_subrs_storage);
1113 plan->inprogress_accelerator->destroy_cff_accelerator =
1114 cff_subset_accelerator_t::destroy;
1115
1116 }
